    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Here is the text for Section 4.2: \"4.2 Price Adjustments: While the base rate is fixed for the duration of the term, the Supplier reserves the right to implement a temporary surcharge of up to 5% during peak demand months (defined in Exhibit B) to account for market volatility. Such adjustments shall be applied to the invoices issued during said months.\"\n\nDoes this clause give them the right to just hike the price on us without us agreeing to it first? I really can't have the budget swinging like that.",
