      "content": "I just checked Exhibit B. It's pretty vague, but it basically says the months are whenever fuel demand is highest. \n\nLook, I'm in a rush to get this approved by the VP. The main thing is, does this section 4.2 allow them to change the rates *unilaterally*? Like, do they have the right to just change the price without us needing to sign off on a new agreement or something? I need a straight answer so I can tell the board everything is under control.",
